     <body>
     <div type="poem">
   <head>To the Papist Reader.</head>
   <l>TVsh (will the Popish Reader say) th'are lies,</l>
   <l>Professed Apologues, slaunders, all may see:</l>
   <l>I grant 'tis so; And yet as I surmize,</l>
   <l>Tis with a matter of truth ye slandred be.</l>
   <l>
      <pb facs="5"/>Your truest Legends are but tales Canoniz'd,</l>
   <l>Your serious workes ridiculous to view:</l>
   <l>His falsest tales are stories but mispriz'd,</l>
   <l>And why may not the man which laughes speake true.</l>
   <lg>
      <l>Only for this vntruth I must him blame,</l>
      <l>In that he giues the truth a lyers name:</l>
      <l>Only in this I needs must say he failes,</l>
      <l>And tels a tale in that he calls them tales.</l>
   </lg>
   <closer>
      <signed>I. H.</signed>
   </closer>
</div>
